---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — basic camera" description="Privacy Policy for basic — a priority-mode camera for iPhone. Your data, photos, and settings remain entirely yours, processed locally.">
  <div style="background:#000;color:#F3EEE3;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'SF Pro Text','Helvetica Neue',Arial,sans-serif;overflow-x:hidden;min-height:100vh;">

    <!-- ============ NAV ============ -->
    <nav class="navbar">
      <a href="/" style="text-decoration:none;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;">
        <img src="/icon-120.png" style="width:24px;height:24px;border-radius:5px;object-fit:cover;" alt="basic logo" />
        <span style="font-size:19px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.5px;color:#F3EEE3;">basic</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-menu">
        <a href="/" class="nav-btn">Home</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- ============ CONTENT ============ -->
    <main style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:120px 24px 80px;">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:11px;letter-spacing:3px;color:#C9A35B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;">App Store Compliant</div>
      <h1 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-weight:400;font-size:42px;line-height:1.1;letter-spacing:-1px;margin:0 0 8px;color:#F3EEE3;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(243,238,227,.42);margin-bottom:48px;">Last Updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="legal-body" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(243,238,227,.78);">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.7;color:#F3EEE3;font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:32px;">
          basic is designed with a simple, non-negotiable philosophy: the frame is the interface, and your data is none of our business.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-size:24px;color:#F3EEE3;margin:40px 0 16px;font-weight:500;">1. Zero Data Collection & Transmission</h2>
        <p>
          We do not collect, monitor, store, or transmit your personal data. <strong>basic operates 100% offline</strong>.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No Accounts:</strong> You do not need to register, sign in, or provide an email address to use the app.</li>
          <li><strong>No Analytics:</strong> We use no tracking code, third-party analytics SDKs, or cookies. We have no mechanism to track how often you launch the app, what exposure settings you select, or which lenses you shoot with.</li>
          <li><strong>No Server Transfers:</strong> Your images are processed entirely on-device using local system APIs (AVFoundation and PhotoKit). No pixels, files, or telemetry are ever uploaded to our servers or shared with any third party.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-size:24px;color:#F3EEE3;margin:40px 0 16px;font-weight:500;">2. Device Access & System Permissions</h2>
        <p>
          To capture and save photos, the app requires standard Apple iOS system permissions. You maintain full control over these permissions:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Camera Permission:</strong> Required strictly to initialize the sensor, render the live viewfinder, and capture image frames (RAW/JPEG).</li>
          <li><strong>Photo Library (PhotoKit) Permission:</strong> Required strictly to write captured image files to your iOS Photo Library, and to display the thumbnail of your last captured shot in the gallery button.</li>
          <li><strong>Location Services (Optional):</strong> If you choose to grant location permissions, they are used solely to attach GPS coordinates to the EXIF metadata of the files saved locally in your library. We do not store or transmit your location.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-size:24px;color:#F3EEE3;margin:40px 0 16px;font-weight:500;">3. Payments & Transaction Data</h2>
        <p>
          App purchases and upgrades are processed securely and directly by Apple via the App Store. We do not receive, store, or have access to your payment details, billing information, or billing address. All transactions are governed by Apple's App Store Privacy Policy.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-size:24px;color:#F3EEE3;margin:40px 0 16px;font-weight:500;">4. Legacy Content & Data Portability</h2>
        <p>
          Since <strong>basic</strong> writes directly to your Apple Photo Library (using standard iOS system directories and PhotoKit structures), any photo you shoot is preserved as a native asset on your device.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No Cloud Locking:</strong> Your photos are not locked in a proprietary cloud or app-specific sandbox. JPEGs and Apple ProRAW DNG files are stored directly in your iCloud Photo Library (if enabled) or local storage.</li>
          <li><strong>Data Preservation:</strong> If you choose to delete basic, your photos and legacy content remain safely in your iOS Photo Library. We have no server backups, meaning we cannot recover deleted photos, nor do we have access to them. You are solely responsible for ensuring your device is backed up via iCloud or physical connection.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-size:24px;color:#F3EEE3;margin:40px 0 16px;font-weight:500;">5. GDPR, CCPA, and Global Compliance</h2>
        <p>
          Because we do not collect, process, or store any personal data, basic is inherently compliant with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and other worldwide data privacy frameworks. You cannot exercise "right to be forgotten" requests because we possess no data to forget.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:'Spectral',Georgia,serif;font-size:24px;color:#F3EEE3;margin:40px 0 16px;font-weight:500;">6. Contact & Inquiries</h2>
        <p>
          For questions, support, or privacy inquiries:
          <br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:hello@thebasic.camera" style="color:#C9A35B;text-decoration:none;">hello@thebasic.camera</a>
          <br />
          Operated by Raastey (<a href="https://raastey.co" style="color:#C9A35B;text-decoration:none;">raastey.co</a>).
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>

    <!-- ============ FOOTER ============ -->
    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="footer-container">
        <div>
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;">
            <img src="/icon-120.png" style="width:24px;height:24px;border-radius:5px;object-fit:cover;" alt="basic logo" />
            <span style="font-size:18px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.5px;">basic</span>
          </div>
          <div style="font-size:14px;color:rgba(243,238,227,.5);line-height:1.6;">a priority-mode camera for iPhone<br />a <a href="https://raastey.co" style="color:#C9A35B;text-decoration:none;">raastey.co</a> venture</div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:60px;font-size:14px;">
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;">
            <span class="mono" style="color:rgba(243,238,227,.4);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.5px;">LEGAL</span>
            <a href="/terms" style="color:rgba(243,238,227,.62);text-decoration:none;">Terms of Service</a>
            <a href="/privacy" style="color:#C9A35B;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Privacy Policy</a>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;">
            <span class="mono" style="color:rgba(243,238,227,.4);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.5px;">CONTACT</span>
            <a href="mailto:hello@thebasic.camera" style="color:rgba(243,238,227,.62);text-decoration:none;">hello@thebasic.camera</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mono" style="max-width:1280px;margin:40px auto 0;font-size:12px;color:rgba(243,238,227,.32);letter-spacing:.5px;">© 2026 thebasic.camera</div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .navbar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,.55);
    backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.07);
  }
  .nav-menu {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .nav-btn {
    color: #0a0a0b;
    background: #C9A35B;
    padding: 9px 17px;
    border-radius: 9px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background-color .2s ease, transform .2s ease;
  }
  .nav-btn:hover {
    background: #e5ba6a;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  
  .legal-body ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .legal-body li {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal-body strong {
    color: #F3EEE3;
  }

  .footer {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(243,238,227,.07);
    padding: 60px 24px 40px;
    background: #060606;
  }
  .footer-container {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 769px) {
    .navbar {
      padding: 18px 40px;
    }
    .footer {
      padding: 80px 64px 40px;
    }
    .footer-container {
      flex-direction: row;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }
  }
</style>
